'''李绳武'''（Li Shengwu<ref>{{cite web |author1=Harvard University |title=Shengwu Li |url=https://economics.harvard.edu/people/shengwu-li |access-date=2020-08-11 |archive-date=2021-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118012038/https://economics.harvard.edu/people/shengwu-li |dead-url=no }}</ref>，{{bd|1985年|}}），[[客家人|客家裔]][[新加坡華人|新加坡華人]]，[[新加坡|新加坡]]公民<ref name="#1">{{cite news |author1=Lydia Lam |title=Li Shengwu found guilty of contempt of court, fined S$15,000 or a week's jail if he does not pay |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/li-shengwu-fined-15000-default-week-jail-contempt-of-court-12971994?cid=h3_referral_inarticlelinks_24082018_cna}}</ref>；[[经济学|经济学]]者，[[李光耀|李光耀]]之孙，[[李显扬|李显扬]]之长子。

== 生平 ==
2009年，获[[牛津大学|牛津大学]][[哲学、政治学及经济学|哲学、政治学及经济学]][[学士|学士]]学位，一等荣誉毕业。

2011年，获牛津大学经济学[[硕士|硕士]]学位，荣誉毕业。

2016年，获[[斯坦福大学|斯坦福大学]]经济学[[博士|博士]]学位，师从日后的[[诺贝尔经济学奖得主|诺贝尔经济学奖得主]][[保罗·米尔格龙|保罗·米尔格龙]]（Paul Robert Milgrom）(2020年)和Muriel Niederle，研究经济理论，[[行为经济学|行为经济学]]，[[实验经济学|实验经济学]]。

2016年至2018年，任[[哈佛大学|哈佛大学]]学会学者（Harvard Society of Fellow）。

2018年起，任哈佛大学经济学[[助理教授|助理教授]]。

曾于经济学顶级刊物，American Economic Review，Journal of Political Economy等发表论文。

擅长[[辩论|辩论]]，[[牛津大学辩论社|牛津大学辩论社]]，斯坦福大学辩论教练。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Shengwu Li |title=Shengwu Li |url=https://www.shengwu.li/ |access-date=2020-08-11 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127231045/https://www.shengwu.li/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2017年，李绳武在[[脸书|脸书]]上转发了一条[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]的评论文章，并附言道“当然，要牢記，[[新加坡政府|新加坡政府]]好讼，而且有一个聽話的[[法院|法院]]體系”（ "Keep in mind, of course, that the Singapore government is very litigious and has a pliant court system."）。2020年7月29日，新加坡法庭判决李绳武[[藐视法庭|藐视法庭]]，罚款15000[[新加坡元|新加坡元]]或入狱[[监禁|监禁]]一周，另需要支付16570新加坡元法庭诉讼相关费用。<ref name="#1"/>李绳武“选择支付罚款，以避免新加坡政府借此攻击他和他的家人”（"Paying the fine avoids giving the Singapore Government an easy excuse to attack me and my family"），“换来一些安宁”（ "in order to buy some peace and quiet"），<ref>{{cite news |author1=Lydia Lam |title=Li Shengwu to pay S$15,000 fine for contempt of court but does not admit guilt |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/li-shengwu-to-pay-s-15-000-fine-for-contempt-of-court-but-does-13009676 |accessdate=2020-08-11 |archive-date=2020-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201007155156/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/li-shengwu-to-pay-s-15-000-fine-for-contempt-of-court-but-does-13009676 |dead-url=no }}</ref>但他“不认罪”（"not admit guilt" ）<ref>{{cite news |author1=法新社 |title=Singapore PM’s nephew Li Shengwu to pay contempt of court fine but won’t admit guilt |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3096875/singapore-pms-nephew-li-shengwu-pay-contempt-court-fine |accessdate=2020-08-11 |archive-date=2021-01-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210101180841/https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3096875/singapore-pms-nephew-li-shengwu-pay-contempt-court-fine |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

